Demonstrate your understanding of this Sprint's concepts by answering the following free-form questions. Edit this document to include your answers after each question. Make sure to leave a blank line above and below your answer so it is clear and easy to read by your project manager.

 Explain the differences between client-side routing and server-side routing.

Server-side routing is requesting information from an external server and then receiving that information in response, reloading the entire page in the process.
Client-side routing is requesting different pieces of information from within the application, without a full page reload in response to an external server request. 

 Which HTTP methods can be mapped to the CRUD acronym that we use when interfacing with APIs/Servers.

C, create, is a POST method which adds data to storage
R, read, GET method retreives data from server
U, update, PUT updates or changes information on server
D, delete, DELETE method deletes an entry from server

 Mention three tools we can use to make AJAX requests.

 We can use JQUery with the $.ajax function,
 the Fetch API
 or Axios.